 the big <br />changes are), I felt it was more important to get that lining up than it <br />was to see the first part of the filename.<br /><br />But yeah, we should probably have a flag to allow longer (and shorter) <br />lines, and another to control whether we truncate to strictly honor that <br />flag or not.<br /><br />That said, I think the current behaviour is likely at least the right <br />default one. It's quite readable once you get used to it, and the renames <br />do _not_ get truncated in the "summary" part at the end, since then there <br />is nothing to line up with.<br /><br />So for an example of this, just do<br /><br />	git show --summary --stat -M 06a36db1<br /><br />where you have an already fairly long pathname that is then renamed to <br />_another_ long pathname.<br /><br />		Linus<br />-<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.kernel.org<br />More majordomo info at  <a href="http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html">http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html</a><br />Please read the FAQ at  <a href="http://www.tux.org/lkml/">http://www.tux.org/lkml/</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
